Cause even if I don’t agree with the fuckshit that is identity politics I knew some of the queer women friends I have who put their bodies on the frontlines did so knowing that if they died Angel Nduka-Nwosu will honor them in death.

I knew that shit was gonna come down because again I am a researcher so I know when a pattern of sacrifice will hurt.

Let me not lie I documented Endsars primarily from a vexed and selfish perspective.

These men understood that an Igbo woman like me having her name with a hashtag like #endsars can and will do and undo even in the East.

Angel on a normal day will say fuck shit I’m not gonna talk on EndSars cause I know as a conflict researcher that minority groups sacrificing and begging to be seen as human always ends in tears.

in the eyes of media boys.
